-- out/todo.txt --
Structural cycles are reported in all chains compared to old implementation.

b4.b: In evalv3 the structural error is converted to an eval error (conflicting values),
   which is correct. evalv2 did not report this error.

b6.b.a.0.0: evalv2 reports an additional structural cycle error here, evalv3 does not.

b7.b.0.0: evalv3 correctly reports an eval error (conflicting values); the structural
   cycle is nested one too deep before detection in evalv2.

b10.c.d: evalv3 allows b: string in the position, which is correct.

d1: evalv3 reports the error at d1.r, evalv2 at d1.a.b.c.d.t.

d2: evalv2 additionally reports d2.r.c.d.t as structural cycle.

d3: evalv3 reports at d3.x.indirect, evalv2 at d3.x.a.b.c.

e3: evalv2 additionally reports e3.a.c and e3.b.c as structural cycles.

e4: evalv2 reports 4 errors in empty disjunction; evalv3 reports 2.

fieldsSumInfinite.issue3310: evalv3 correctly spots a structural cycle;
   evalv2 computes an incorrect result without erroring.

issue2545: the source comment says the optional field should break the cycle and
   this should succeed. Both v2 and v3 report a structural cycle; this is an open bug.

nestedList.v1e/v2e: evalv2/evalv3 differ in error message details for empty disjunction.

resolveToAncestor.t1.X: evalv2 reports both a and b as cyclic; evalv3 only reports b.

shortPathFail.comprehension: evalv2 shows a disjunction in tail; evalv3 shows null.

shortPathFail.elipsis.t1: evalv2 shows a disjunction in #Foo.ref; evalv3 shows null.

withLetFail: evalv2 attributes error to _schema_1, evalv3 to schema.next.

z1.z: evalv2 reports z1.z.f.h and z1.z.g.h; evalv3 reports z1.z.g.

b12: evalv3 shows a tail disjunction in the innermost list1 node; evalv2 shows null.

n4: field ordering differs between evalv2 and evalv3.
